===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|dett|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|dete|lang=fro}} (French: {{term|dette|lang=fr}}), from {{etyl|ML.|en}} {{m|la|dēbita}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|dēbitum||what is owed, a debt, a duty}}, neuter of {{m|la|dēbitus}}, perfect passive participle of {{m|la|dēbeō||I owe}}, contraction of {{m|la|*dehibeō||I have from}}, from {{term|de||from|lang=la}} + {{m|la|habeō||I have}}.

The unpronounced "b" in the modern English spelling is a [[Latinisation]] from the Latin etymon {{m|la|dēbitum}}.

